    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Claytonia acaulis are indigestion, which can be alleviated due to its high mucilage content that soothes the digestive tract, and skin irritations, such as eczema and acne, that can be treated with its anti-inflammatory properties. Claytonia acaulis is also effective in reducing fever in cases of colds and flu, thanks to its ability to increase sweating, which helps to cool the body. Furthermore, its antiseptic and antimicrobial properties make it an effective treatment for wounds, preventing infection and promoting faster healing. Claytonia acaulis has been used to alleviate respiratory issues such as bronchitis and asthma, by reducing inflammation and congestion. Additionally, its demulcent properties make it an effective treatment for sore throats, by coating and soothing the mucous membranes.",
