    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Claytonia acaulis are antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial. Antioxidant properties of Claytonia acaulis are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, which help protect against cell damage and oxidative stress. The anti-inflammatory properties of this plant are associated with the bioactive compounds such as saponins and glycosides, which have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. Furthermore, the antimicrobial properties of Claytonia acaulis are due to the presence of volatile oils, which exhibit bactericidal and fungicidal activities, making it effective against various pathogens. Additionally, the antiviral properties of this plant are attributed to the presence of terpenoids and alkaloids, which have been shown to inhibit the replication of certain viruses.",
