    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Claytonia acaulis are flavonoids, phenolic acids, terpenoids, and saponins. Flavonoids have been shown to possess antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties, making them effective in reducing inflammation and promoting wound healing. Phenolic acids, such as ferulic acid, have been found to exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, as well as the ability to inhibit the growth of certain microorganisms. Terpenoids, including limonene and beta-pinene, have been demonstrated to possess antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and antioxidant properties, contributing to their potential in treating various health conditions. Saponins, particularly a saponin glycoside called clatonia saponin, have been reported to exhibit antimicrobial, antioxidant, and anti-inflammatory activities, which may help in reducing inflammation and promoting tissue repair.",
